---
export interface Props {
  /** Variant: 'full' for dedicated page, 'compact' for homepage band */
  variant?: 'full' | 'compact';
}
const { variant = 'full' } = Astro.props;
---
<article class:list={[
  'border border-oastl-forest/20 bg-oastl-cream rounded-sm',
  variant === 'full' ? 'p-8 md:p-10 grid gap-8 md:grid-cols-[220px,1fr] items-start' : 'p-6 grid gap-5 md:grid-cols-[120px,1fr] items-start',
]}>
  <div class="w-full">
    <img
      src="/images/books/oregons-constitutional-duties-2025.jpg"
      alt="Oregon's Constitutional Duties to Schools (2025) — book cover"
      loading="lazy"
      class="w-full h-auto rounded-sm border border-oastl-forest/20 shadow-sm"
    />
  </div>
  <div>
    <div class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-oastl-gold mb-3">
      OASTL Founding Scholarship · 2025
    </div>
    <h3 class:list={[
      'font-serif font-semibold text-oastl-forest leading-tight',
      variant === 'full' ? 'text-3xl md:text-4xl' : 'text-2xl',
    ]}>
      <em>Oregon’s Constitutional Duties to Schools</em>
    </h3>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-oastl-ink/70 font-mono uppercase tracking-wide">
      by Margaret Bird &amp; Dave Sullivan
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 text-[15px] md:text-base text-oastl-ink/85 leading-relaxed">
      {variant === 'full' ? (
        <>
          Co-authored by OASTL board members Margaret Bird and Dave Sullivan,
          <em> Oregon’s Constitutional Duties to Schools </em>
          uncovers the billion-dollar betrayal of Oregon’s school trust lands and demands accountability.
          The book is the Oregon-specific peer to the broader campus’s founding scholarship —
          <em> Schools of the Republic </em> at the Library and
          <em> The Eighth Anchor </em> at the Institute.
          Available free as a PDF download; also available on Amazon in Kindle, paperback, and hardback formats.
        </>
      ) : (
        <>
          The Oregon-specific case for fiduciary accountability. The billion-dollar betrayal of Oregon’s school trust lands, and the constitutional argument for restoring them.
        </>
      )}
    </p>
    <div class="mt-5 flex flex-wrap gap-3 text-sm">
      <a
        href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1E1IhBgk8fdtKnQd2FqkFqE9V1xduYd0u/view?usp=sharing"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 rounded-sm border border-oastl-forest bg-oastl-forest text-oastl-cream px-4 py-2 hover:bg-oastl-canopy"
      >
        Download free PDF
      </a>
      <a
        href="https://a.co/d/8PpB6f8"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 rounded-sm border border-oastl-forest/40 text-oastl-forest px-4 py-2 hover:border-oastl-gold hover:text-oastl-gold"
      >
        Order from Amazon
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</article>
